The paper deals with sparse data models and their use in signal and image processing tasks. The proposed framework for designing sparsity regularization terms is based on tools from universal coding theory, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the practical advantages of the proposed framework in image denoising, zooming, and classification, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper presents examples of image processing tasks, which can be categorized under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
